reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Cute and Classy Small Hoop
reviews.reviewText: This hoop is cute and classy, and I enjoy the hinge opening quite a bit. I took away one star as the hoop could benefit being just a bit larger to accommodate anyone with a detached (i.e. larger) lobe. The bottom of the hoop on the inside touched the edge of my lobe. Definitely adds to any outfit, especially in a work/business casual environment.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute, classy, and comfortable!
reviews.reviewText: I freaking love these earrings! Being gold plated sterling silver, they are perfect for sensitive skin! They dip a little lower than a classic huggy earring, which I really like! They are lightweight and don't feel like they are weighing down your ears at all. The way the earrings are made, it ensures that there's nothing poking you in the back of your head behind your ear. You can wear these even while you sleep and have full confidence and comfort. :-) I chose the white color option, I'm not much of a bright color girl, and I really like that they can go with basically anything I wear – quite the versatility!My Star Rating Rubric:5 ⭐️ - Perfect! reviews.reviewText: Love these! Wanted small hoops I coujld leave in that would not pull down my ears. Super lightweight. Clip shut but aren't hard to remove. Comfy enough to sleep in. Small and dainty, look just like the pics.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars WELL MADE QUALITY EARRINGS; VERY SMALL
reviews.reviewText: When I opened the box, it was obvious these earrings are well made. They are nicely polished and the enamel is even. The posts are an adequate length, nicely soldered, and stamped "925". The latch backs work well and are easy to use. They are lightweight and comfortable. However, they are quite small, approximately 1/2" long, 1/8" wide, and 7/16" deep (measurement from front of earring to back). I do wish I had not chosen pink because that color tends to blend in with my natural skin tone, making them more difficult to see. They do have a dainty presence.I believe the posts are sterling silver. From a careful reading of the website it appears the rest of the earring is likely a base metal with white gold plating. That said, they are quality earrings and I will enjoy wearing them. PAVOI is American owned.
